From 4bf2a373e7bd4baaf8c317a01cba41da2a437d81 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: baseballyama <xydybaseball@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 14:30:45 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] fix: don't mistake `type` identifier expressions for TS
 `type` declarations in tags

Detect TypeScript `type` declarations by actually parsing instead of by
character-class blacklists, so that expressions like `{type === 'all' ? a : b}`
or `{type instanceof Foo}` aren't misclassified as malformed declarations.

Closes #18328
